name: uncle martin's
address: 94M3+799, Beraban, Kediri, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: The Coffee, The Atmosphere and Mas Doni is very informative about the product and easy going as well. Definitely will be back again!
review 2: A hidden gem of Bali. It is a fun place to scooter to and then be welcomed into a lovely home to experience someone with a real passion for their craft. Not only serving coffee (who sources the beans around indonesia and roasts himself) but also a selection of teas (red rice tea was delicious), chocolate, and cacao. Drink with a serene view next to rice fields.
review 3: Great ambience, great coffee, great talk.
review 4: #latepost A hidden gem in Tabanan. Great coffee and scenery in a humble & cozy place with friendly owner. Sipping coffee while enjoying afternoon breeze here is highly recommended.
review 5: We had a great time at Uncle Martin’s coffee. No electricity, nice ambience, and Donny is a humble owner. Can’t wait to go back!

name: Henrynatha guesthouse
address: Jl. Galiran, Beraban, tanah lot, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Stayed here for a month! One of the best accommodations near Canggu area. The place is clean, new, with everything that you need. Great swimming pool and view on rice terraces. Located in a quite area, you can easily get from here to canggu/seseh. The host couple is very friendly, ready to help you with everything, so you can feel like at home here. Highly recommend
review 2: The place was perfect for us. Our stay at Henrynatha guesthouse was excellent. The place is new, clean, and well-maintained. Facilities work perfectly, and the boutique-style decor, along with rooftop access, was a pleasant surprise. It's conveniently located, with Seseh beach nearby and Changgu just a 15-minute drive away. The couple who runs the place is friendly, accommodating, and treated us like family. Great place to escape to if you’re wanting more quietude and pristine vistas without sacrificing convenience and access to what Changgu has to offer. Highly recommended for a comfortable and enjoyable stay.
review 3: comfortable place to stay, special for the upper rooms, we can see the sunrise in the morning, we also get a view of green rice fields, the facilities are also good, there is a swimming pool too, only 5 minutes to Tanah Lot Temple, I really recommend this place to stay
review 4: A comfortable place to stay, the rooms are spacious and clean.  The bed is comfortable, smells good... a good place to see the sunset from the 2nd floor
review 5: New Spot with spacious and comfortable room, has a really view of the rice fields with sunrise and sunset, good location and far from the crowds, recommended !
